data.title: Fuck you Death. She was only 35....

images.description: My friend, contracted covid recently... she didn't make it. No preexisting conditions. Healthy up until she got the virus. Her last month has been difficult. While in hospital she suffered a heart attack, almost had to have a leg amputated, and at the end her organs shut down. The Dr's did everything they could to help. Multiple surgeries and treatments, but it just wasn't enough to save her.
She would light up any room with her smile. Loved to game, and was into photography.
I will miss you friend.

data.title: Docs To Georgia Senators: 'Shame On You' For Not Passing COVID-19 Relief

images.description:
Georgia recorded 5,023 new cases of COVID-19 on Friday, breaking previous single-day records, according to the state health department. Officials reported 43 new deaths Friday, which brings the state's total number of deaths to 8,922.

"Every single N95 mask that a health care worker has to reuse through an entire shift because stocks are low only puts us and the people we care for at risk," Dr. Kate Miele, an Atlanta OB-GYN said. "By refusing to pass COVID-19 relief, Sens. Perdue and Loeffler are turning their backs on every Georgian, including every health care worker in our state."

MontaDr. Eduardo Montaña, a pediatric cardiology specialist in Mariettaña called the senators' inaction a travesty, and said they need to pass the revised $908 billion Health and Economic Recovery Omnibus Emergency Solutions Act or Heroes Act.

data.description: I was on TV tonight. A semi-local TV station was doing a piece on our local Xmas tree "gathering". All the local businesses decorate a tree in the town green. Well a TV station was recording. Myself, my wife and my 10 month son were interviewed. The interview did not make it on TV but our images did. And well shit, I have let myself go and it so fucking sad. I need to get back in shape. And maybe this is a wake up call. We shall see.

images.description:
Good things about a giant cat: more to love! More personality! More hilarity!

Bad things about a giant cat: when something goes wrong it can go REALLY wrong. He went from being my sweet shadow to being Cujo in cat form. I had to lock him in my bathroom like he was Old Yeller in the corn crib. The vet put him on phenobarbital and it’s working! He’s back to his normal sweet, funny, loving self!
He loves to sleep near me.
He’s a good boy. My best boy. His name is Duncan & he’s a Maine Coon.
Love you all!!

data.title: After 25 years of bulimia, 6 years of alcoholism, and being severely overweight

images.description:
I hired a personal trainer. I lost the weight about 10 years ago, but I've still been struggling with the bulimia and alcohol. I decided to ask someone to kick my ass, and she's been awesome. This is the first time in 10 years I've seen healthy muscle mass on my body, and sorry it's a selfie but I want people who are struggling to know that no matter how low you get, you can still get better. My journey isn't nearly over, but for me this is huge progress.

Edit: Imgur, you never cease to impress me with your kindness and support. I've gotten 20+ messages asking what "severely overweight" means, so here you go: http://imgur.com/a/Bg4arqT
